1,500m Olympic Champion Faith Chepngetich did not disappoint Kenyans once again as she raced to her second consecutive gold at the Olympics.  She also did it in style as she set a new Olympic record of 3:53.11 at the Olympic Stadium in Tokyo, Japan on Friday.  Netherland’s Sifan Hassan who Kenyans had feared would spoil Kenya’s party could not keep up witFaith in the last 300m and finished in third place with Laura Muir of Great Britain and Northern Ireland finishing in second place. More to follow..  Man City sign Grealish from Aston Villa in British record Sh15 billion deal  Burkina Faso wins first-ever Olympic medal  Lionel Messi potential destinations  Time for Kipchoge to hit back at Tokyo Olympics  Here are countries with the highest cash rewards to athletes - and where Kenya stands By Bismarck Mutahi in Tokyo, Japan | 55 minutes ago By Washington Onyango | 1 hour ago By Washington Onyango | 1 hour ago By Bismarck Mutahi in Tokyo, Japan | 2 hours ago